cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.OS

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the optimization of network resources for live migration of VMs over 5G FOGRAN MPTCP connections.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper deals with the migration of VMs between Fog data centers and wireless devices, which involves distributed computing.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes an optimal minimum-energy Settable-Complexity Bandwidth Manager for live migration of VMs, which involves control systems.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the energy consumption of wireless devices, which may involve hardware optimization.
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with the implementation of the proposed SCBM in software, which may involve operating system optimization.
